{"lemma":"سكِيت","slug":"سكِيت","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20200","n20202","n20203"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%83%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AA"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20200","headword_ar":"سُكَيْتٌ","root":"skt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sik~iytN","text_ar":"سِكِّيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ukayotu","text_ar":"السُّكَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uk~ayotu","text_ar":"السُّكَّيْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) sometimes pronounced thus with teshdeed, (S,) the former being the more common, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tenth horse in a race;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the last of them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the last horse among those that start together in a race,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the ten that are reckoned;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfisokil~u","text_ar":"الفِسْكِلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaA$uwru","text_ar":"القَاشُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; those that come in after this one not being reckoned. (S.) The other nine are thus called, beginning with the first of these:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almujal~iY","text_ar":"المُجَلِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuSal~iY","text_ar":"المُصَلِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almusal~iY","text_ar":"المُسَلِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aAliY","text_ar":"التَّالِى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmurotaAHu","text_ar":"المُرْتَاحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaATifu","text_ar":"العَاطِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaZiY~u","text_ar":"الحَظِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuw^am~alu","text_ar":"المُوَمَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~aTiymu","text_ar":"اللَّطِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Sb says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukayotN","text_ar":"سُكَيْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a contracted dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suk~ayotN","text_ar":"سُكَّيْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the uncontracted dim. of which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukayokiytN","text_ar":"سُكَيْكِيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN sukayotu AlHalobapi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ سُكَيْتُ الحَلْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the tenth horse of those that are started together for a wager"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is scrupulously nice and exact,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and therefore deliberate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his handicraft."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20202","headword_ar":"سُكَّيْتٌ","root":"skt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sik~iytN","text_ar":"سِكِّيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uk~ayotu","text_ar":"السُّكَّيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ukayotu","text_ar":"السُّكَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n20203","headword_ar":"سِكِّيتٌ","root":"skt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAkuwtN","text_ar":"سَاكُوتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakuwtN","text_ar":"سَكُوتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukayotN","text_ar":"سُكَيْتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suk~ayotN","text_ar":"سُكَّيْتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sikotiytN","text_ar":"سِكْتِيتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAkuwtapN","text_ar":"سَاكُوتَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [all intensive epithets, and the last doubly intensive,] A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constantly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continually, silent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in explanation of the first and second:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often, silent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in explanation of the first, and K in explanation of all above-cited therefrom,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restraining himself from speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakotN","text_ar":"سَكْتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (K:) and ↓ this last, [which is originally an inf. n., and therefore used as an intensive epithet, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] (AZ, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAkuwtN","text_ar":"سَاكُوتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAkuwtapN","text_ar":"سَاكُوتَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakotapN","text_ar":"سَكْتَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [but the last, which is written in the TA without any syll. signs, is doubly intensive, as is also that next preceding it,] a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who speaks little,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without inability to express his mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to express what he would say,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and, when he speaks, does so well."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA","AZ"]}]}}